The storage facility I bought in August had no gate and no fence. 

I’m spending $91K to gate and fence the property. 

So… is it worth the money? 

Personally, I think so. I’ve owned storage with and without gates / fences (called access control in the industry)

And I’ll say that you get better results with a gate controlled by a keypad and a fenced property. 

Maybe it’s just the perception that comes with a property that has access control and prevents the riff raff from coming onto your property.
